Text.SourceString: Hello, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>… Nice to meet you too. I’m <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Hello, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>… Nice to meet you too. I’m <NPCName>Valentina</>.

Text.LocalizedString: Umm… Yeah, it’s really fun here.//<portrait=happy>You get to fly kites and build snowmen in Winter!

Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes school is boring.//<portrait=annoyed>You read all these hard books all the time. Blech!

Text.LocalizedString: I saw Uncle <NPCName>Rafael</> yesterday. He came to visit us at the inn.//<portrait=annoyed>Every time I see him, he always asks me about school… Like every week!

Text.LocalizedString: I play at the beach with <NPCName>Oliver</> after school.//<portrait=happy>So much fun!//<portrait=normal>But then, we get hungry after a while, so we go home.

Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Emma</> makes the yummiest fish tacos!//Sometimes she comes to our class and just hands them out to us for free.

Text.LocalizedString: He also said sometimes grown-ups don't even know what they wanna be.//That's okay too…

Text.LocalizedString: I'm not gonna cut my hair, ever. I want it to be super long like Mom's.

Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> used to live with us at the inn, but now he stays at Hillside Vineyard.

Text.LocalizedString: Mom said Hillside Vineyard is better for <NPCName>Taco</>, 'cause he can run around and play with other animals.

Text.LocalizedString: I gotta be super careful about what I take from the forest, 'cause there are mushrooms there that could make you sick.

Text.LocalizedString: I'm only allowed to go to the forest with an adult, like Aunt <NPCName>Alice</>, or when <NPCName>Archie</> asks his dad to go with us.

Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> taught us how to make kites. She’s my friend’s mom, and she’s pretty cool.//She came to school on Career Day to talk about carpentry.

Text.LocalizedString: I learned a lot about trees, cutting wood, and making things that day.

Text.LocalizedString: But when it’s festival time, he takes a day off to play with me for the whole day!//<portrait=normal>Pretty cool, huh?

Text.LocalizedString: You’re not small, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>! Someday, I’m going to be big and strong too.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I wish Mom could play with me more and not be so busy with the inn.//<portrait=doubt>Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> is not that fun. I don’t wanna play with her too much.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I wish Mom could play with me more and not be so busy with the inn.//<portrait=doubt>Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> is not that fun. I don’t wanna play with her too much.

Text.SourceString: I think if Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> had a daughter, she’d look like me… Don’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: I think if Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> had a daughter, she’d look like me… Don’t you?

Text.SourceString: You’re a really cool farmer, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a really cool farmer, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> is really cool too. He knows a lot about bugs!//<portrait=normal>You should ask him bug questions. I bet he could tell you the answer right away.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> is really cool too. He knows a lot about bugs!//<portrait=normal>You should ask him bug questions. I bet he could tell you the answer right away.

Text.SourceString: I was just thinking about <NPCName>Nina</>'s fancy hats.
Text.LocalizedString: I was just thinking about <NPCName>Nina</>'s fancy hats.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, so… <NPCName>Nina</> said I could borrow her hats for dress-up.//She has so many that I can use some for my snowmen. Do you have fancy hats too?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, so… <NPCName>Nina</> said I could borrow her hats for dress-up.//She has so many that I can use some for my snowmen. Do you have fancy hats too?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</> likes to play in the fountain.//<portrait=normal>Mom said it’s okay because he’s a dog.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</> likes to play in the fountain.//<portrait=normal>Mom said it’s okay because he’s a dog.

Text.SourceString: But if he can't get out, I gotta get a grown-up to help.
Text.LocalizedString: But if he can't get out, I gotta get a grown-up to help.

Text.SourceString: Mom doesn't like it when I use her stuff to dress up the scarecrows.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom doesn't like it when I use her stuff to dress up the scarecrows.

Text.SourceString: My clothes are too small, so I gotta use hers.
Text.LocalizedString: My clothes are too small, so I gotta use hers.

Text.SourceString: I've started writing all my best jokes and riddles.//One day, I'll put them in a book.
Text.LocalizedString: I've started writing all my best jokes and riddles.//One day, I'll put them in a book.

Text.SourceString: Then I'll sell the book and get loads of money to buy my own inn.
Text.LocalizedString: Then I'll sell the book and get loads of money to buy my own inn.

Text.SourceString: I have a riddle for you, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>. What’s cute and fuzzy?
Text.LocalizedString: I have a riddle for you, <PlayerName>$honorifics $player</>. What’s cute and fuzzy?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</>! He’s cute and fuzzy… Ah, that one’s definitely going in my book.//<portrait=doubt>Hmm… It could be <NPCName>Bonbon</> too, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</>! He’s cute and fuzzy… Ah, that one’s definitely going in my book.//<portrait=doubt>Hmm… It could be <NPCName>Bonbon</> too, I guess.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really play with Peanut and Butter. They don’t go out very much.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really play with Peanut and Butter. They don’t go out very much.

Text.SourceString: Also, they always run away every time I try to pet them.
Text.LocalizedString: Also, they always run away every time I try to pet them.

Text.SourceString: If you have good farmer jokes, let me know. I might put them in my book.
Text.LocalizedString: If you have good farmer jokes, let me know. I might put them in my book.

Text.SourceString: If I publish it and we’re famous, we can make another one so we get even more famous!
Text.LocalizedString: If I publish it and we’re famous, we can make another one so we get even more famous!

Text.SourceString: I’m busy collecting riddles and jokes right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m busy collecting riddles and jokes right now.

Text.SourceString: I think I can give this to <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> as my writing project.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I can give this to <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> as my writing project.

Text.SourceString: I found some cool shells today at the beach. Ah… A good day.
Text.LocalizedString: I found some cool shells today at the beach. Ah… A good day.

Text.SourceString: They’re super colorful. Wanna see?
Text.LocalizedString: They’re super colorful. Wanna see?

Text.SourceString: How many scarecrows do you have on your farm? I want to keep one in my room.
Text.LocalizedString: How many scarecrows do you have on your farm? I want to keep one in my room.

Text.SourceString: I’m not good at mini golf yet, but Dad says I have a strong swing.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not good at mini golf yet, but Dad says I have a strong swing.

Text.SourceString: One day, when I'm all grown up, I wanna buy my own island.//Me, Mom, and all my pets will live there!
Text.LocalizedString: One day, when I'm all grown up, I wanna buy my own island.//Me, Mom, and all my pets will live there!

Text.SourceString: And maybe Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> can come too, but then who's gonna run the inn?
Text.LocalizedString: And maybe Aunt <NPCName>Alice</> can come too, but then who's gonna run the inn?

Text.SourceString: I’m going to write the prettiest poem in the world and send it to Nana.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to write the prettiest poem in the world and send it to Nana.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Ling</> taught us there are tools underwater to see if our coral reefs are healthy.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Ling</> taught us there are tools underwater to see if our coral reefs are healthy.

Text.SourceString: Um… They’re called beacons… It sounds like “bacon!”//Anyway, there’s also all kinds of magical kelp that can help our island get healthier.
Text.LocalizedString: Um… They’re called beacons… It sounds like “bacon!”//Anyway, there’s also all kinds of magical kelp that can help our island get healthier.

Text.SourceString: She didn’t exactly say the word “magical.” But they sound magical, don’t they?
Text.LocalizedString: She didn’t exactly say the word “magical.” But they sound magical, don’t they?

Text.SourceString: I’m going to paint the prettiest painting in the world. It’ll have birds, and all kinds of flowers, and robot scarecrows.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to paint the prettiest painting in the world. It’ll have birds, and all kinds of flowers, and robot scarecrows.

Text.SourceString: Maybe not today… I’m having too much fun.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe not today… I’m having too much fun.

Text.SourceString: I still don’t know what I wanna be when I grow up.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll be a blacksmith like Nana and Papa!
Text.LocalizedString: I still don’t know what I wanna be when I grow up.//<portrait=happy>Maybe I’ll be a blacksmith like Nana and Papa!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> plays with his dad in the forest after school.//<portrait=normal>He told me <NPCName>Joko</> is teaching him all kinds of stuff like fishing and making clocks.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> plays with his dad in the forest after school.//<portrait=normal>He told me <NPCName>Joko</> is teaching him all kinds of stuff like fishing and making clocks.

Text.SourceString: That’s pretty cool! I kinda wish my dad could be around more to teach me cool things.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s pretty cool! I kinda wish my dad could be around more to teach me cool things.

Text.SourceString: Green smoothies are okay.//<portrait=annoyed>They don’t taste terrible, but I wish Mom would just stop making them.
Text.LocalizedString: Green smoothies are okay.//<portrait=annoyed>They don’t taste terrible, but I wish Mom would just stop making them.

Text.SourceString: Yuck…
Text.LocalizedString: Yuck…

Text.SourceString: Mom says a wool hat isn’t for snowmen.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom says a wool hat isn’t for snowmen.

Text.SourceString: Well, if a wool hat won’t do, Mom’s green scarf might look fancy on my snowman.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, if a wool hat won’t do, Mom’s green scarf might look fancy on my snowman.

Text.SourceString: I don’t feel like playing mini golf today.//So I think I’ll just play around here.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t feel like playing mini golf today.//So I think I’ll just play around here.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Oliver</> always has cookies in his pocket, and he always shares with us.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Oliver</> always has cookies in his pocket, and he always shares with us.

Text.SourceString: I never ever want to leave. I want to live with Mom forever and ever!
Text.LocalizedString: I never ever want to leave. I want to live with Mom forever and ever!

Text.SourceString: Eggplant lasagna is okay.//<portrait=annoyed>It's...alright, I guess. It doesn't taste terrible, but I wish Mom would stop making it. Yuck!
Text.LocalizedString: Eggplant lasagna is okay.//<portrait=annoyed>It's...alright, I guess. It doesn't taste terrible, but I wish Mom would stop making it. Yuck!

Text.SourceString: Yay, snow!
Text.LocalizedString: Yay, snow!

Text.SourceString: See ya later, alligator!
Text.LocalizedString: See ya later, alligator!

Text.SourceString: Do you know where to get a mistletoe?//I want to bring it when I visit Nana and Papa.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know where to get a mistletoe?//I want to bring it when I visit Nana and Papa.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna make them kiss.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna make them kiss.

Text.SourceString: I don't like going to my uncle's house in the Summer.//It's super-duper hot there.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't like going to my uncle's house in the Summer.//It's super-duper hot there.

Text.SourceString: I like going to Dad’s house. Nana and Papa live right next door, and I get to see them all the time!//<portrait=happy>Plus, in the Summer, Nana always has lots of starfruits growing in her garden.
Text.LocalizedString: I like going to Dad’s house. Nana and Papa live right next door, and I get to see them all the time!//<portrait=happy>Plus, in the Summer, Nana always has lots of starfruits growing in her garden.

Text.SourceString: It’s fun here too, but at Dad’s house, I get to plant all kinds of things.//Flowers…starfruits! Dad has a garden at his house.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s fun here too, but at Dad’s house, I get to plant all kinds of things.//Flowers…starfruits! Dad has a garden at his house.

Text.SourceString: Some of my clothes are still at Dad’s house.//I keep my fairy dress there because Nana and I put on fairy dresses in Spring and bless the garden before we start planting for the year.//<portrait=happy>Nana is cool!
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my clothes are still at Dad’s house.//I keep my fairy dress there because Nana and I put on fairy dresses in Spring and bless the garden before we start planting for the year.//<portrait=happy>Nana is cool!

Text.SourceString: Mom borrows Aunt <NPCName>Alice’s</> boots sometimes.//They’re very pretty and comfy. I wanna wear them too when my feet are bigger.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom borrows Aunt <NPCName>Alice’s</> boots sometimes.//They’re very pretty and comfy. I wanna wear them too when my feet are bigger.
